                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Update Notes: January 14, 2005 1/14/2005 7:00 AM 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">*** Gameplay *** </span>
<br />

<br />
- Changed the level of some boss encounters to better match the zone they inhabit. Rewards should also be more appropriate for the level of the encounter. 
<br />
- Certain difficult encounters (such as those made famous by Professor Cogglesworth) will now drop a wider variety of loot. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">*** Spells & Combat Arts *** </span>
<br />

<br />
Conjurer 
<br />
- L39 Vexation: Will now replenish power and health over time. 
<br />
- L40 Geotic Brand: This spell will now increase armor class instead of decreasing it. 
<br />
- L30 Tremor: Will now show up in the maintained window. 
<br />

<br />
Necromancer 
<br />
- L22 Blight: Spell will show in the maintained window. 
<br />
- L30 Breath of the Unearthed: Will now only affect members of the target encounter, and deals disease damage and heals the Necromancer over time. 
<br />
- L31 Withering Affliction: Will now show in the maintained window. 
<br />
- L38 Rotting Thrall: Fixed description; it summons a zombie to do the Necromancer's bidding 
<br />
- L44 Accursed Cloud: Will now only affect members of the target encounter, and deals disease damage and heals the Necromancer over time. 
<br />

<br />
Bruiser 
<br />
- L37 Rousing Cry: Will now affect other party members who are within range of the Bruiser. 
<br />
- L20(Training) Velan's Nervy Order: Will now affect other party members who are within range of the Bruiser. 
<br />
- L40 Heavy Scarring: Fixed description; it stuns the Bruiser while greatly increasing Crushing, Slashing, and Piercing mitigations. 
<br />

<br />
Berserker 
<br />
- L26 Stifled Rage: Apprentice IV versions of Stifled Rage should now work properly. 
<br />
- L24 Battle Chant: Apprentice IV versions of Battle Chant should now work properly. 
<br />

<br />
Brawler 
<br />
- L10(Training) Velan's Taunting Cry: Now shares same reuse timer as all other group taunts (Shout, Jeer, Hand Clap, etc.). 
<br />

<br />
Paladin 
<br />
- L36 Smite Prayer: Corrected the skill required from 115 to 180. 
<br />

<br />
Brigand 
<br />
- L36 Sap: Can now be used regardless of the Brigand's position relative to the target. 
<br />
- L27 Rough Skin: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />
- L40 Deceit: Now grants the Brigand a 30% chance to interrupt the target on successful attacks. 
<br />
- L41 Aegis: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Rogue 
<br />
- L13 Street Smarts: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Predator 
<br />
- L13 Hunter's Instinct: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Assassin 
<br />
- L27 Bleeder's Talent: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />
- L41 Merciless Villainy: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Ranger 
<br />
- L27 Forester's Insight: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />
- L41 Veil of the Forest: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Swashbuckler 
<br />
- L27 Flight of Fancy: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />
- L41 Bladeweaver: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Dirge 
<br />
- L27 Death's Scent: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />
- L41 Lithe Disbelief: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Troubador 
<br />
- L41 Daelis' Dance of Blades: Increased growth from 30 skill to 50. 
<br />

<br />
Fury 
<br />
- L47 Irritating Swarm: This spell will now land on the target and other surrounding encounter members.
<br />

<br />
- The EverQuest II Team</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Quote of the Week:</span> 
